content:
The initial prompt is now changed to output "Full contents of /absolute/path/to/file" before the contents of a file, instead of making it a command like "cat << 'EOF' >"

So when a command block is started, pass in the previous line of text to the command parser. If that line has "contents of /absolute/path/to/file" then yes that is a command and you can parse out the common d path from it.

Just change the command parsing for now.

Return full files and executable commands.

Modify the components that call parseCommand. 

Return full files and executable commands.
